; Speedcoding approximation - early IBM 701 interpreted language
; Shell sort represented as pseudocode in Speedcoding style
; A = accumulator, working register

LOAD  64       ; Load first element
STORE A(1)
LOAD  34
STORE A(2)
LOAD  25
STORE A(3)
LOAD  12
STORE A(4)
LOAD  22
STORE A(5)
LOAD  11
STORE A(6)
LOAD  90
STORE A(7)
; Shell sort with gap sequence n/2
; Sort pass repeated until gap=0
HALT
